            <h1 class="section__header">Yoga at FIT-TRACK</h1>
            <p class="section__description">
                Discover inner peace and physical well-being through our diverse yoga classes. Our experienced instructors will guide you through a journey of mindfulness, flexibility, and strength-building practices.
            </p>

            <div class="yoga-types">
                <h2>Types of Yoga Classes</h2>
                <p>At FIT-TRACK, we offer various yoga styles to cater to different needs and preferences:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Hatha Yoga:</strong> A gentle, classic yoga style focusing on postures and breathing.</li>
                    <li><strong>Vinyasa Flow:</strong> A dynamic practice linking breath with movement.</li>
                    <li><strong>Yin Yoga:</strong> A slow-paced style with poses held for longer periods.</li>
                    <li><strong>Power Yoga:</strong> A vigorous, fitness-based approach to yoga.</li>
                    <li><strong>Restorative Yoga:</strong> A relaxing practice using props to support the body.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="yoga-benefits">
                <h2>Benefits of Yoga</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Improves flexibility and balance</li>
                    <li>Builds strength and muscle tone</li>
                    <li>Reduces stress and promotes relaxation</li>
                    <li>Enhances mental clarity and focus</li>
                    <li>Improves posture and body awareness</li>
                    <li>Boosts overall well-being and energy levels</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="yoga-poses">
                <h2>Basic Yoga Poses</h2>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/pic1.jpg" alt="Mountain Pose">
                    
                        <div class="pose-description">
                            <h3>1. Mountain Pose (Tadasana)</h3>
                            <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                            <p>
                                1. Stand with feet together and arms by your sides.<br>
                                2. Press your feet into the ground and lift your chest up.<br>
                                3. Reach the crown of your head toward the ceiling and relax your shoulders.<br>
                                4. Keep the spine aligned and breathe deeply.
                            </p>
                        
                            <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                            <p>Improves posture, strengthens legs, and promotes balance and calmness.</p>
                        </div>
                        
                </div>

                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/adho mukha.jpg" alt="Downward Facing Dog">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>2. Downward Facing Dog (Adho Mukha Svanasana)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Start on your hands and knees in a tabletop position.<br>
                            2. Lift your hips towards the ceiling, straightening your legs.<br>
                            3. Press your hands into the mat and keep your head between your arms.<br>
                            4. Push your heels toward the ground (they may not touch initially).
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Stretches the hamstrings, calves, and shoulders; strengthens arms and legs; improves circulation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/balasana.jpg" alt="Child's Pose">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>3. Child's Pose (Balasana)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Kneel on the floor with your big toes touching and knees apart.<br>
                            2. Sit back on your heels and extend your arms forward.<br>
                            3. Rest your forehead on the mat and breathe deeply.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Stretches the back, calms the mind, relieves stress, and lengthens the spine.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/virabhadra 1.jpg" alt="Warrior I">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>4. Warrior I (Virabhadrasana I)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Step one foot forward into a lunge and bend the front knee.<br>
                            2. Keep the back leg straight with the heel on the ground.<br>
                            3. Raise your arms overhead and face forward.<br>
                            4. Hold for a few breaths, then switch sides.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens legs, opens hips, and improves focus and balance.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/virabhadra 2.jpg" alt="Warrior II">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>5. Warrior II (Virabhadrasana II)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Step one foot forward, bending the knee.<br>
                            2. Extend your arms parallel to the floor.<br>
                            3. Turn your head to look over your front hand.<br>
                            4. Keep your back leg straight and grounded.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens the legs, opens the hips, improves balance and concentration.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/trikonasana.jpg" alt="Triangle Pose">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>6. Triangle Pose (Trikonasana)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Stand with your feet wide apart.<br>
                            2. Turn one foot out 90 degrees and extend your arms at shoulder height.<br>
                            3. Reach forward with the front hand and lower it to your shin or the floor.<br>
                            4. Extend the opposite arm upward and look at your raised hand.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Stretches legs, hips, and torso; strengthens the legs; improves digestion.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/setu bandhasana.jpg" alt="Bridge Pose">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>7. Bridge Pose (Setu Bandhasana)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor.<br>
                            2. Place your arms by your sides and press into your feet to lift your hips.<br>
                            3. Roll your shoulders underneath you and clasp your hands beneath your body.<br>
                            4. Hold for a few breaths, then lower slowly.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens the back, glutes, and hamstrings; opens the chest and shoulders.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/marjaryasana-bitilasana.jpg" alt="Cat-Cow Pose">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>8. Cat-Cow Pose (Marjaryasana-Bitilasana)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Begin on all fours in a tabletop position.<br>
                            2. On an inhale, arch your back (cow pose) and lift your head and tailbone.<br>
                            3. On an exhale, round your back (cat pose) and tuck your chin toward your chest.<br>
                            4. Repeat the flow with your breath.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Improves flexibility of the spine, massages internal organs, and relieves stress.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/bhujangasana.jpg" alt="Cobra Pose">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>9. Cobra Pose (Bhujangasana)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Lie on your stomach with your hands under your shoulders.<br>
                            2. Press into your palms to lift your chest, keeping elbows slightly bent.<br>
                            3. Engage your back muscles and keep your legs on the floor.<br>
                            4. Hold and breathe, then release back down.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens the spine, opens the chest, and relieves fatigue.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="yoga-pose">
                    <img src="/image/assets/yoga/paschimottanasana.jpg" alt="Seated Forward Bend">
                    <div class="pose-description">
                        <h3>10. Seated Forward Bend (Paschimottanasana)</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            1. Sit with legs extended in front of you.<br>
                            2. Inhale and lengthen your spine, then exhale and fold forward over your legs.<br>
                            3. Reach for your feet or shins, and relax your head toward your knees.<br>
                            4. Hold and breathe deeply.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Stretches the spine, hamstrings, and lower back; calms the mind.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                
